2. EDRDG KANJIDIC2 open data

The public bundle includes an unmodified, hash-pinned KANJIDIC2 snapshot and
the corresponding EDRDG licence text at:

    open-data/kanjidic2.xml.gz
    open-data/EDRDG-LICENSE.html

KANJIDIC2 is produced by the Electronic Dictionary Research and Development
Group (EDRDG).  It is distributed under the EDRDG licence, currently Creative
Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0).

Project pages:
    https://www.edrdg.org/wiki/index.php/KANJIDIC_Project
    https://www.edrdg.org/edrdg/licence.html
    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

The bundle manifest records the exact snapshot SHA-256, database version, and
creation date.  Builder-derived structural records identify KANJIDIC2 as their
source.  This project's personal-use terms do not reduce rights granted directly
by EDRDG under CC BY-SA 4.0.

EDRDG also requires software using its dictionary files to provide a regular
update procedure.  Snapshot pinning is used for reproducible builds, not to
freeze an obsolete dictionary indefinitely.  Maintainers check the upstream
KANJIDIC2 and licence at least monthly and publish a refreshed compatible public
release when either file changes.  End users update by installing the newest
public-builder release and its matching bundle.

